We have recommended that Management should implement policies and control procedures in the granting and liquidation of cash advances through the following:

Stop the granting of cash advance to official or employee unless the previous cash advance given to him/her is first settled or a proper accounting thereof is made in compliance with the above-referred provisions of PD1445;

Regularly send confirmation/demand letters as basis in the reconciliation of accounting and accountable officers record and as basis in imposing disciplinary measures;

Strictly comply with COA Circular No. 2012-004 for long outstanding accounts.

Furnish the Audit Team with the list of accountable officers with unliquidated and outstanding cash advances, together with copy of written notices duly acknowledged by the accountable officers.  Submit also copies of disbursement vouchers (DVs) and related supporting documents of those officers with outstanding balances, especially with long overdue accounts.

